Obtaining Help	

	You can always use the --help flag on each ofs the actions. That will 
print a brief explation of each of the flags. 


Help

	This action prints a basic help showing all available actions

----------------------------------------
sdm help
----------------------------------------

----------------------------------------
-> % sdm help                                                       
Usage: sdm <action>

Actions:
   install
   help
----------------------------------------

Install

	This action installs a deliverable on your disk into your current directory:

----------------------------------------
sdm install -a some_file.xml 
----------------------------------------

	This action installs a deliverable on your disk into /var/tmp:

----------------------------------------
sdm install -a some_file.xml -r /var/tmp
----------------------------------------

	This action installs a deliverable on your disk into your current directory using a remote ADM file:

----------------------------------------
sdm install --remote -a http://www.orpiske.net/path/to/some/file.xml
----------------------------------------

	This action installs a deliverable on your disk into /var/tmp using a remote ADM file:

----------------------------------------
sdm install --remote -a http://www.orpiske.net/path/to/some/file.xml -r /var/tmp
----------------------------------------